🚨 Microsoft Alert: Windows 11 Updates May Trigger BitLocker Recovery Prompt 🔐💻

Some recent Windows 11 updates are causing devices to request the BitLocker recovery key during startup. This happens when Windows detects changes in system security, such as firmware updates, BIOS changes, or certain cumulative updates.

🔍 Why This Happens
* BitLocker thinks the system's security state has changed
* TPM (Trusted Platform Module) may revalidate device integrity
* Windows update triggers a security handshake failure
* System asks for the recovery key to confirm authorized access

⚠️ Why You Should Act Now
If you don’t have your BitLocker recovery key saved, you could be locked out of your PC.

✅ Do This Immediately
* Save your BitLocker recovery key securely
* Check your Microsoft account
* Backup your key to cloud or external storage
* Verify TPM/BIOS settings after updates

